<%# Sidekiq breakdown — two semantic groupings rendered as two separate
    `.stack-table`s (2026-05-17 polish, extracted to this component
    2026-05-18 per Beta-3 lane B candidate B9).

    Two distinct tables:
      * lifetime counters (successful / failed) — 2-column data
      * queue counters (busy / scheduled / enqueued / retry / dead) — 5-column

    Both share `table-layout: fixed` with a shared 5-column colgroup so
    the 2-col lifetime row aligns with the 5-col queue row below.
    Lifetime fills only cols 3 + 5 → `successful` lands under `enqueued`,
    `failed` lands under `dead`. Cols 1, 2, 4 are spacer cells.

    Beta 4 F3-D — per-cell tonal class via `color_class_for(state)`:

      busy       → tui-chip--success  (green)
      enqueued   → tui-chip--warn     (orange)
      retry/dead → tui-chip--danger   (pink)
      failed     → tui-chip--danger   (pink)
      scheduled  → tui-chip--neutral  (muted)
      processed  → default text color

    Cells with a zero count roll back to `tui-chip--neutral` so green /
    orange / pink only surface on a real signal — matches the
    status-bar Sidekiq segment's `.sk-zero` behavior.

    The wrapping `<div>` carries the pair so the vertical spacing reads
    as one Redis-stats block. %>
<div style="margin-bottom: 8px;">
  <table class="stack-table" style="table-layout: fixed; width: 100%;">
    <colgroup>
      <col style="width: 20%;">
      <col style="width: 20%;">
      <col style="width: 20%;">
      <col style="width: 20%;">
      <col style="width: 20%;">
    </colgroup>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th class="num"></th>
        <th class="num"></th>
        <th class="num">successful</th>
        <th class="num"></th>
        <th class="num">failed</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td class="num"></td>
        <td class="num"></td>
        <td class="num <%= color_class_for("processed") %>" data-stack-stats-live-target="successful">
          <%= cell_for("processed") %>
        </td>
        <td class="num"></td>
        <td class="num <%= color_class_for("failed") %>" data-stack-stats-live-target="failed">
          <%= cell_for("failed") %>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <table class="stack-table" style="margin-top: 6px; table-layout: fixed; width: 100%;">
    <colgroup>
      <col style="width: 20%;">
      <col style="width: 20%;">
      <col style="width: 20%;">
      <col style="width: 20%;">
      <col style="width: 20%;">
    </colgroup>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th class="num">busy</th>
        <th class="num">scheduled</th>
        <th class="num">enqueued</th>
        <th class="num">retry</th>
        <th class="num">dead</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <% QUEUE_STATES.each do |state| %>
          <td class="num <%= color_class_for(state) %>" data-stack-stats-live-target="<%= state %>">
            <%= cell_for(state) %>
          </td>
        <% end %>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>
